nodes.text: Longfang was a term which meant the leader of a group, or pack.

It was used by the Barabel Saba Sebatyne to describe how when Alema Rar, Jaina Solo, and Zekk had abandoned their posts, the Jedi Council could not make a firm decision on what to do, because it had more than one leader. It was later used by Saba when referring to Master Skywalker before the Battle of Kuat.
